==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Struthiones
<hw>Stru`thi*o"nes</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[NL.
See <er>Struthio</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>A
division, or order, of birds, including only the African
ostriches.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>In a wider sense, an extensive group
of birds including the ostriches, cassowaries, emus, moas, and allied
birds incapable of flight. In this sense it is equivalent to
<ord>Ratitae</ord>, or <ord>Dromaeognathae</ord>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Struthionine</ent>⟦br⟧
